com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents

Interface XMLSerializable.OldVersionCompatible

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPluginDocument, AlignmentLayout, CmlDocument, CombinedAlignmentAndAminoAcidSequenceDocument, CombinedAlignmentAndNucleotideGraphSequenceDocument, CombinedAlignmentAndNucleotideSequenceDocument, CombinedAlignmentAndSequenceDocument, DefaultAlignmentDocument, DefaultAminoAcidSequence, DefaultMolecularStructureDocument, DefaultNucleotideGraphSequence, DefaultNucleotideSequence, DefaultPhylogenyDocument, DefaultSameTaxaTreesDocument, DefaultSequenceDocument, DefaultSequenceListDocument, DefaultTreeDocument, DocumentCollection, DocumentField, EValue, FolderView, GprDocument, HinDocument, ImmutableSequence, ImmutableSequenceImplementation, Interval, MolDocument, NwoDocument, OligoSequenceDocument, OperationRecordDocument, PairedReadManager, PdbDocument, Percentage, PhylogenyDocument, SequenceAnnotation, SequenceCharSequence, SequenceListOnDisk, SequenceListOnDisk.AlignmentData, SequenceListSummary, SequencePropertiesStorage, SequenceSelection, SequenceSelection.SelectionInterval, SequenceSelection.SequenceIndex, SequenceSelectionWithDocuments, SequenceSelectionWithDocuments.ExtractionStrategy, SequenceTrack.Manager, ValueAndFrequencyDistribution, XyzDocument
    Enclosing interface:
    XMLSerializable

    public static interface XMLSerializable.OldVersionCompatible
    XMLSerializable classes may implement this to indicate they support serializing to older version formats and potentially deserializing from newer version formats.

    This interface should usually only be implemented by classes bundled with Geneious. Classes and PluginDocument implementations that aren't bundled with Geneious (for example 3rd party plugins) may wish to implement this interface too, so that documents they create can be used in older versions of Geneious. But they also need to implement their own version support system in their XML. This is because those plugins can be installed with any version of Geneious and users are able to downgrade the version of a non-bundled plugin without downgrading Geneious.

    When implementing this interface calls to getVersionSupport should use Geneious.MajorVersion.max() with an appropriate value for their own XML changes combined with the values returned from all classes they depend on.

    Since:
    API 4.600 (Geneious 6.0.0)

      • toXML

        org.jdom.Element toXML(Geneious.MajorVersion majorVersion,
                     ProgressListener progressListener)
        Serializes this class to XML format, potentially to a format readable by an earlier version of Geneious. It is acceptable for the XML to include unnecessary tags that will be ignored by the earlier version. For example if the implementation has only extended the XML since the earlier version, then the XML returned may be identical to the XML returned for the current version.

        See XMLSerializable.toXML() for a more detailed description of what it means to serialize to XML.

        All classes that implement this method must also implement XMLSerializable.toXML() and should delegate back to this method using Geneious.getMajorVersion() and ProgressListener.EMPTY as parameters.

        Parameters:
        majorVersion - the major version of Geneious to serialize to XML for. For example "6.0" but not "6.0.0". This must be a version returned greater or equal to a version returned from getVersionSupport(VersionSupportType.OldestVersionSerializableTo) and must never be greater than the current version (Geneious.getMajorVersion())
        progressListener - for reporting progress and cancelling
        Returns:
        object encoded as a JDOM element
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - whose cause is a XMLSerializationException if the serializable class is a PluginDocument and it is unable to serialize to a temporary file using PluginDocument.FILE_DATA_ATTRIBUTE_NAME.
